Former Eskom chairperson Jabu Mabuza died on Wednesday, apparently as a result of Covid-19 complications. He is survived by his wife and three children. SABC broke the news on Wednesday night, and TimesLIVE was able to independently confirm his passing. Sandile Zungu, president of the Black Business Council, also confirmed the news in an interview with the SABC. Mabuza wasÂ previously the group  CEO of Tsogo Sun Holdings Limited, and was also  president of Business Unity SA. He served on boards of  companies across SA. Eskom spokesperson Sikonathi Mantshantsha said the power utility would not  comment until it was able to confirm the news, and would issue a statement on Thursday morning. TimesLIVE